laboratory_examinations.findings: The liver is diffusely echogenic with a smooth contour and no focal liver mass. There is focal fatty sparing along the gallbladder edge. The main portal vein is patent with hepatopetal flow. No ascites. No intrahepatic biliary dilation. The visualized portion of the common bile duct measures 6 mm. Stones in the distended gallbladder with mild asymmetric wall edema (3-4 mm thick). No pericholecystic fluid. Positive sonographic Murphy's sign.
Mixed bacterial flora (>= 3 colony types), consistent with skin and/or genital contamination.
